To compile and run this code you need:

-An Nvidia graphics card with CUDA capability on your computer
-Use Linux (with X-window system installed)
-Have CUDA installed, see https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads
-Have freeglut installed (do sudo apt-get install freeglut3-dev on Debian/Ubuntu)

To compile the code, then go to ./Debug and run "make all"

Make sure the lidar sends its data on port 2368, or change the port in LidarObstacleVisualizer.cu a recompile

Click and drag to pan camera, zoom with scroll wheel, and type 'q' to quit

To see a demo on how this looks if you get it to work see https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yWAGOXomGlw 
